				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The only time you'll ever get $0D in practice is if you're using $2D or $3D. Those colors are nearly identical to $00 and $10 respectively on an NTSC or PAL NES, but they show up black (identical to $xE or $xF) on an RGB PPU, such as the one in <a href="http://www.disgruntleddesigner.com/chrisc/gotRGB/fctitler.html" class="postlink">Famicom Titler</a> or PlayChoice 10. Do any licensed games actually use those grays, or would they have failed lot check? I haven't tried injecting code into Nintendo's official emulator to see if they show up.</div>

